 Ken Katzman, vice president of 
trade marketing at Dover Publications, explains how a 
traditional book publisher can compete in an increasingly 
digital world. Katzman also offers his perspective on the future
of Barnes & Noble, and explains how Mineola, New York-based 
Dover Publications is growing its traditional business. Katzman 
talks with Bloomberg's Vonnie Quinn on Bloomberg Radio's "The 
Hays Advantage."  (Source: Bloomberg)  Running time 16:13
 